# Tabnine Context Engine

When the user asks about code in remote repositories, wants to search across multiple repos, or needs to understand how a service or module works across the codebase, use the Tabnine Context Engine MCP tools.

## Available Tools

- **`remote_repositories_list`** — List all indexed repos
- **`remote_codebase_search`** — Semantic + lexical code search across repos
- **`remote_symbol_content`** — Find symbols with full source code
- **`remote_symbols_search`** — Search for functions, classes, enums by name
- **`remote_file_content`** — Fetch file contents from remote repos
- **`remote_files_search`** — Search files by path/name
- **`remote_repository_folder_tree`** — Browse repo directory structure
- **`remote_search_assets`** — Search OpenAPI specs and service summaries
- **`remote_openapi_spec_query`** — Query OpenAPI specs with jq expressions
- **`remote_get_asset`** — Get full asset content
- **`remote_grep_asset`** — Grep through asset content with regex

## When to Use

- User asks "how does X work" about a remote service
- User wants to find implementations across repos
- User asks about API endpoints or service contracts
- User needs to understand architecture or data flow
- User asks to search for specific code patterns across the codebase
- User asks about dependencies between services

See the `remote-repositories-context` skill for detailed instructions on how to use the available tools and workflow patterns.
